Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @Poblano Pepper{1} crosswise into strips. Trim and
thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%tsp} in a large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add @Ground Plant-Based Protein{6%oz} and season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.
Cook ~{5-8%minutes}, breaking up protein into pieces, until browned and warmed
through. Remove from heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add poblano and
cook, stirring, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If needed, add a splash of water to help poblano soften.

Use pan used for plant-based protein here.

While poblano cooks, drain and rinse @Black Beans{1%13.4oz can}.

Once poblano is softened, stir in scallion whites and @Southwest Spice Blend{2%tsp}
(4 tsp for 4 servings). (Be sure to measure the Southwest Spice; we sent more.)
Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add beans, @Tex-Mex Paste{1%unit}, and 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4). Cook,
stirring, until filling has combined and thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once poblano is softened, stir in plant-based protein. Cook through remaining
step as instructed.

Sprinkle bean filling with @Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup} and @Mexican Cheese Blend{1/2%cup}.
Cover pan until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Wrap @Flour Tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with bean filling, @Smoky Red Pepper Crema{2%tbsp},
and scallion greens. Serve.